usly, the ConAgra facility has developed an OSHA hazardous substance emergency response program called Emergency Action Plan. This document was developed in accordance with 29 CFR 1910.38 and 29 CFR 1910.120(q).

The plan includes procedures for the response to an ammonia release, including:  

1.)	Hazardous Material Response; 
2.)	Roles and Lines of Authority; 
3.)	Emergency Recognition and Prevention; 
4.)	Safe Distances and Places of Refuge; 
5.)	Site Security and Control; 
6.)	Medical First Aid; 
7.)	Decontamination; 
8.)	Personal Protective Equipment; and
9.)	Critique of Emergency Action Plan and Follow-up.

The Emergency Action Plan consists of all notifications and plant evacuation procedures in the event of an ammonia release.  

7.0	PLANNED CHANGES TO IMPROVE SAFETY

Based on the completed Process Hazard Analysis (PHA) for ammonia, a list of action items to improve safety was developed and their status monitored to ensure that implementation was accomplished.
